cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use IAGA Sentinel, please cite it as below."
title: "IAGA Sentinel"
abstract: >-
  An EU AI Act conformity-evidence layer for AI agents: it inspects
  governance-relevant agent actions and turns each verdict into an Ed25519-signed,
  hash-chained receipt that verifies offline.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Bambini
    given-names: Edoardo
  - family-names: Petteni
    given-names: William
  - family-names: Bohr
    given-names: Justus Moritz
version: "1.8.0"
date-released: "2026-06-22"
license: BUSL-1.1
repository-code: "https://github.com/EdoardoBambini/IAGA-Sentinel"
url: "https://www.iaga.tech"
keywords:
  - ai-agents
  - ai-governance
  - eu-ai-act
  - audit
  - cryptographic-receipts
  - tamper-evident-logging
